		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Gandalf Lewis Style - DPC Atlanta Winner</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='95' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/lotr/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(4.77)</font> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23089&PHPSESSID=e0de22364fdcb3e3d17eb180d82b750d">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=1041">Steven "Sir Yoda" Lewis</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=1041&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This has been my deck (in one form or another) since before Mines came out and has won me every single tournament I have won including the 2002 Atlanta LOTR Master Series tournament.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> May 2, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> STARTING<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(175)">Frodo, Son of Drogo</a><br />
One Ring, Isildur&#39;s Bane<br />
